S3 coef and summary for breathtestfit

Source: R/coef_breathtestfit.R
coef.breathtestfit.Rd

Function coef extracts the estimates such as t50, tlag, from fitted 13C beta exponential models. The result is the same as fit$coef, but without column stat, which always is "estimate" for nls_fit and nlme_fit.

The summary method only extracts t50 by the Maes/Ghoos method

# S3 method for breathtestfit
coef(object, ...)

Arguments

object

of class breathtestfit, as returned by nls_fit or nlme_fit
...

other parameters passed to methods

Examples

# Generate simulated data
data = cleanup_data(simulate_breathtest_data())
# Fit with the population method
fit = nlme_fit(data)
# All coefficients in the long form
coef(fit)
#> # A tibble: 80 x 5
#>    patient_id group parameter method                    value
#>    <chr>      <chr> <chr>     <chr>                     <dbl>
#>  1 rec_01     A     m         exp_beta                18.0   
#>  2 rec_01     A     k         exp_beta                 0.0149
#>  3 rec_01     A     beta      exp_beta                 2.06  
#>  4 rec_01     A     t50       bluck_coward            24.8   
#>  5 rec_01     A     t50       maes_ghoos              83.9   
#>  6 rec_01     A     t50       maes_ghoos_scintigraphy 15.9   
#>  7 rec_01     A     tlag      bluck_coward             1.86  
#>  8 rec_01     A     tlag      maes_ghoos              48.3   
#>  9 rec_02     A     m         exp_beta                29.8   
#> 10 rec_02     A     k         exp_beta                 0.0112
#> # ... with 70 more rows
# Access coefficients directly
fit$coef
#> # A tibble: 80 x 6
#>    patient_id group parameter method                  stat       value
#>    <chr>      <chr> <chr>     <chr>                   <chr>      <dbl>
#>  1 rec_01     A     m         exp_beta                estimate 18.0   
#>  2 rec_01     A     k         exp_beta                estimate  0.0149
#>  3 rec_01     A     beta      exp_beta                estimate  2.06  
#>  4 rec_01     A     t50       bluck_coward            estimate 24.8   
#>  5 rec_01     A     t50       maes_ghoos              estimate 83.9   
#>  6 rec_01     A     t50       maes_ghoos_scintigraphy estimate 15.9   
#>  7 rec_01     A     tlag      bluck_coward            estimate  1.86  
#>  8 rec_01     A     tlag      maes_ghoos              estimate 48.3   
#>  9 rec_02     A     m         exp_beta                estimate 29.8   
#> 10 rec_02     A     k         exp_beta                estimate  0.0112
#> # ... with 70 more rows
# Only t50 by Maes/Ghoos
# Can also be used with stan fit (slow!)

# NOT RUN {
if (require("breathteststan")) {
  fit = stan_fit(data, iter = 300, chain = 1)
  coef(fit)
  # We get quantiles here in key/value format
  unique(fit$coef$stat)
}
# }
